		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p103">Creating the Engine DLL From source Code</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=103&amp;sid=d071a94c05f986d97bed2ba2db868269#p103"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54&amp;sid=d071a94c05f986d97bed2ba2db868269" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">tpastor</a></strong> &raquo; 08 Abr 2011, 19:43 </p>

			

			<div class="content">This post will help people to build the StandAlone Engine DLL. <br /><br />The engine use some third part APIs like BepuPhyisics. You need to merge all Dlls to make the standAlone Version.<br />This guide supose that you already have the Engine Code working (compiling in visual studio).<br /><br />To make the single DLL you need to donwload an utility software called <span style="font-weight: bold">ILMERGE</span> (Intermediate Language Merger) to combine the dlls. This can be found here <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/downloads/details.aspx?FamilyID=22914587-b4ad-4eae-87cf-b14ae6a939b0" class="postlink">http://www.microsoft.com/downloads/details.aspx?FamilyID=22914587-b4ad-4eae-87cf-b14ae6a939b0</a><br /><br />After install, put it on your system path.<br /><br />To combine the dll, go to the bin folder of your engine compilation (the same place where you find the PloobsEngine.dll) and use the following command<br /><br /><span style="font-style: italic">ilmerge /out:PloobsEngineDebug.dll BEPUphysics.dll JigLibX.dll LTreesLibrary.dll LTreesPipeline.dll PloobsEngine.dll XNAnimation.dll XNAnimationPipeline.dll /xmldocs /keyfile:XNAnimation.snk /ver:1.0.0.0 /log</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">REMEMBER</span>: The DLLs XNAnimationPipeline.dll and LTreesPipeline.dll and the key XNAnimation.snk are not in this folder. You need to pick them and put here.<br />The XNAnimationPipeline.dll and the XNAnimation.snk are in the XNAANIMATION folder (look at the source code layout folders here <a href="http://ploobsengine.codeplex.com/wikipage?title=Technical%20Info" class="postlink">http://ploobsengine.codeplex.com/wikipage?title=Technical%20Info</a> or in the offline docs here <a href="http://ploobsengine.codeplex.com/releases/view/62892" class="postlink">http://ploobsengine.codeplex.com/releases/view/62892</a>). The LTreesPipeline.dll is in the LtreePipeline project under the PloobsEngine (it is integrated with the engine solution, but the pipeline dll is not automaticaly published in the engine bin folder)</div>

			<div id="sig103" class="signature">PloobsEngine<br />Creator and Developer<br />ploobs.com.br/?page_id=1381</div>

		</div>

		
